<div>
<h3 class="bac">Summary</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Location: London</li>
	<li>9 week, rotational programme from June - August</li>
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent) from any degree discipline</li>
	<li>Fluency in English</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">A strategic partner to our business and corporate groups, HR provides the expertise essential for maximizing employees&#39; professional achievement. Working together, the HR Generalist team supported by their specialist partners including recruitment, diversity, learning and development, compensation and benefits and employee relations, provide a comprehensive service to the business.</p>
<p class="bac">At Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America Merrill Lynch, people are our most valuable and important commodity. HR is responsible for ensuring that we attract, develop and retain a world class workforce. HR is integral in ensuring a fair and meritocratic working environment and maintaining a positive team culture that celebrates diversity.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("overview", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">As a Summer Analyst within HR, you will:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Collaborate on projects that contribute to business success by building relationships, knowledge and experience that will open doors to a wide range of future career options and opportunities</li>
	<li>Work with your team to create a competitive advantage, and promote an internal and external reputation for excellence</li>
	<li>Complete 2 rotations, usually across both a generalist and a specialist HR team to develop a broad understanding of the scope of the function and establish an extensive professional network</li>
	<li>Learn how HR can support the business in achieving their goals and provide strategic vision to maximise efficiency and success</li>
	<li>Complete assigned projects and tasks, attend meetings, conference calls and presentations and undertake research, giving you the opportunity to learn how HR supports the business through engagement with our specialist partners.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The programme is designed to help you decide whether our offer matches your aspirations and includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>One week induction and training programme with classroom instruction</li>
	<li>A buddy and mentoring programme</li>
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring global  &amp; divisional presentations by top executives</li>
	<li>On the job training forms a large part of the learning opportunities</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>On track for a minimum of a 2:1 degree classification (or equivalent) from any degree discipline</li>
	<li>Enthusiasm, a desire to learn and an interest in people</li>
	<li>Good communication skills</li>
	<li>Good organisation skills and attention to detail</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

